FBIS4-59120 "drnes091dd_94005" FBIS-NES-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat Asks Government Workers To Remain in Posts 'Arafat Asks Government Workers To Remain in Posts LD1005181794 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 10 May 94 LD1005181794 Algiers Voice of Palestine Arabic BFN [Text] Chairman Yasir 'Arafat, chairman of the PLO Executive Committee and chairman of the Palestinian National Authority, issued today a decision requesting all the brothers working in the government administrations, institutions, and organs in Palestine to remain in their working positions according to the decision of the Executive Committee adopted at an earlier meeting held this month. Following is the text of the decision: The chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, chairman of the Palestinian National Authority, and in accordance with the decision of the PLO Executive Committee issued on 4 May 1994, the powers accorded him, and the prerequisites of national interest, decides the following: 1. The brothers working in all government administrations, institutions, and organs in Palestine should remain at their posts and continue the discharge of their normal duties. 2. The National Authority demands the precise and honest discharge of all responsibilites laid on our shoulders as a whole at this historic period to ensure the proper running of the work and in the service of the children of our struggling people and militant masses. 3. This decision shall be in force from its date and all concerned must be informed.
